Instrumentation is the base of ITOPs.
Core Concepts
Agent
An Agent is an executable application that runs on managed Windows and Linux devices.
An Agent manages devices such as servers, desktop and laptops.
Master Agent

A Master Agent supports additional monitoring, it functions as an SNMP trap listener within the environment, also performs scheduled Ping, URL, and DNS monitoring.
Any existing Agent can be configured as Master Agent.
A client can have multiple master Agents within the network.
Gateway
A Gateway is a virtual appliance that manages devices such as:
#Servers
#Switches
 ##Routers
 ##Firewalls
#Storage
#Virtual Environment
